<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="33" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
This monobasic genus is included in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scirtothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scirtothrips</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="153 - 17" title="Phylogenetic relationships between some genera of Thripidae (Thysanoptera)." volume="15" year="1981 a">Mound and Palmer 1981a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Masumoto, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 33" title="The genus Scirtothrips Shull (Insecta: Thysanoptera: Thripidae) and three related genera in Japan." volume="1552" year="2007">Masumoto and Okajima 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Drepanothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drepanothrips reuteri" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuteri">Drepanothrips reuteri</taxonomicName>
Uzel is easily recognized from other Iranian genera by precense of the 6-segmented antennae. It is known as a pest of grapes in some areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 79" title="Thysanoptera." volume="1" year="1976">Mound et al. 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Masumoto, M" journalOrPublisher="Research Bulletin of Plant Protection Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="25 - 59" title="Key to genera of the subfamily Thripinae (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) associated with Japanese plant quarantine." volume="46" year="2010">Masumoto 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
